NEWCASTLE DISEASE, HOMING PIGEONS - ITALY: OIE
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Tue, 22 Aug 2006
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: OIE Alert message, 18 Aug 2006 [edited]
<http://oie.int/Messages/060818ITA.htm>

Newcastle disease in italy
---------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of Newcastle disease in Italy reported to the
OIE: June 2003).
Information received on 18 Aug 2006 from Dr Romano Marabelli, Head of the
Department for Veterinary Public Health, Nutrition and Food Safety,
Ministry of Public Health, Rome.
Report date: 18 Aug 2006.
Reason for immediate notification: re-occurrence of a listed disease in a
country following a report declaring the outbreak(s) ended.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 18 Aug 2006.
Date of start of the event: 16 Aug 2006.
Nature of diagnosis: post-mortem and laboratory.
Location of outbreak: Cadoneghe, Padova district, Veneto province.
Number of animals in the outbreak
susceptible: 83.
cases: 1.
deaths: 1.
Description of affected population: homing pigeon.
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Istituto Zooprofilattico
Sperimentale delle Venezie (Padova), OIE Reference Laboratory for Newcastle
disease.
Diagnostic tests used: ICPI [intracerebral pathogenicity index] test.
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measure: quarantine.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[For the location of Cadoneghe, see map at
<http://www.multimap.com/map/browse.cgi?lat=45.4481&lon=11.9092&scale=200000&icon=x>.
The technical data for the performance of the ICPI test are available in
chapter 2.1.15 of OIE's Manual of Diagnostic tests and Vaccines for
Terrestrial Animals, at
<http://oie.int/eng/normes/mmanual/A_00038.htm>. - Mod.AS]
See Also
